news.title: Noida authority demolishes illegal structure in Assotech's housing society
news.para: “Assotech pvt ltd was given permission to built five residential towers in sector 78. In tower H and F the builder had constructed offices and flats illegally. The residents had filed a complaint,” Noida authority said in a statement.

news.title: Anjanapura residents fume over Bengaluru development body's failure to fix potholed road
news.para: The 6.8km stretch links Bannerghatta Road and Kanakapura Road and is the only road for the 3,000-odd residents of Anjanapura to reach the two highways.

news.title: Gunthewari regularisation process rolled out in Aurangabad
news.para: “The civic administration has started the implementation of amended Maharashtra Gunthewari Developments (Regulation, up-gradation and Control) Act. The appointed agencies have been asked to work as per detailed instructions given,” the civic administration has said.

news.title: Nagpur: NMC & NIT dispute prolongs dream of 317 families to construct houses
news.para: The plot owners were running pillar to post to get NIT’s mistakes rectified. The state government withdrew powers of the NIT as a planning authority in August 2019.

news.title: Chandigarh: Administration plots its move for Rs 1,200 crore land
news.para: The administration took possession of the 25-acre land in sectors 52 and 56 eight months back after rehabilitating slum dwellers of tin shed colony.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body issue notices to 3,500 properties
news.para: Prior to slapping them with notices, the civic body had warned the owners to convert the buildings into commercial establishments or stop misusing them.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP revokes OC of Ardee Mall for flouting building plan
news.para: DTCP officials said the developer carried out construction at the mall in violation of the building plan. It also allegedly failed to resolve land disputes and didn’t have complete ownership of the residential colony.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA to send notices to realtors for not submitting reports
news.para: According to the mandatory provision, the promoter have to upload updates on the RERA website for the project at the end of each quarter on apartments/flats, status update of each building.

news.title: Yes Bank-DHFL case: Rana Kapoor's wife, daughter get interim bail
news.para: Kapoor's wife Bindu and daughter Radha were named as accused in the supplementary charge sheet filed by the Central Bureau of Investigation recently, but the duo was never arrested in the case.

news.title: Why Supertech probe roads lead to November 2008 Noida board meeting
news.para: It was through purchasable FAR in 2009 and 2011 that the height of the twin towers, Apex and Ceyane, was increased after the Noida Authority sanctioned amended building plans.

news.title: ED initiates money-laundering probe against Supertech and its chairman
news.para: After Unitech and Amrapali group, Supertech is the third big real estate company that will be investigated by ED under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA).

news.title: Supertech to file review petition against SC order: RK Arora, Chairman
news.para: ​Last week, the apex court had ordered to demolish the twin 40-storey towers, which are part of the Supertech's Emerald Court project in Noida, Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: Illegal sand mining taking place in Goa government's own backyard: Petitioner to HC
news.para: Alvares said that complaints were received that several trucks with illegal sand have been moving out of the directorate of fisheries land in Siolim early morning.

news.title: Haryana government approves OTS scheme for HSIIDC plot defaulters
news.para: HSIIDC, Managing Director, Anurag Agarwal said that a meeting of the Board of Directors of HSIIDC, which was presided over by Principal Secretary to the Chief Minister, V.Umashankar gave go ahead to this agenda.

news.title: Jaipur: Budget hotels' wait for land use change policy gets longer
news.para: Since the existing status of their land is residential, these budget hotels, which account for 80% of the room inventory in the city, are unable to raise money and restart the operations.
